// This note represents the detail process of tensorflow gpu verion installation via conda environment

1. Make sure you have anaconda installed on your ubuntu system
2. Create the virtual environment via conda create -n [env_name]
3. To activate the virtual env ( conda activate [env_name] ), to disable it ( deactivate on win; source deactivate on linux )
4. To use tensorflow gpu version, first install nb_conda and nb_conda_kernels, then we install tensorflow-gpu
5. Activate conda env and run "jupyter-notebook", you good to go!!! 

